      <div class="govspeak">
<h1 id="introduction">Introduction</h1>

<p>Governing bodies, or proprietors of academies and independent schools are required to hold each of these policies and other documents, as outlined, however:</p>

<ul>
  <li>the drafting of school policies can be delegated to any member of school staff</li>
  <li>there is no requirement for all policies to be reviewed annually</li>
  <li>not all policies need to be signed off by the full governing body</li>
</ul>

<p>This document also covers how often each policy must be reviewed and shows the level of approval required, where this is prescribed in regulations. Where it does not we advise you to look at each policy annually, and where there’s a change in the law or circumstances revised your policies or documentation accordingly.</p>

<p>There are instances where statutory guidance states that policies and procedures should be in place. Although this is not the same as a legal requirement, this document makes clear the policies referenced in statutory guidance.</p>

<p>Academies and free schools have greater freedoms than maintained schools in relation to school policies and other documents. Where relevant, arrangements applying to these schools are outlined in legislation or in their funding agreements, which may vary between individual academies and free schools.</p>

<h2 id="administration-and-staff">Administration and staff</h2>

<h3 id="admission-arrangements">Admission arrangements</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Applies to voluntary-aided schools and foundation schools directly and to community and voluntary-controlled schools if the local authority formally delegates the responsibility.</p>

<p>Arrangements for review to be determined annually. Any changes must be consulted on and where no changes are made, consultation is required at least every seven years.</p>

<p>Full governing body or a committee of the governing body to approve, where the school is an admissions authority.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-code">School Admissions Code</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-admissions-appeals-code">School Admission Appeals Code</a>.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/summer-born-children-school-admission">Summer born children school admissions</a></p>

<h3 id="accessibility-plan">Accessibility plan</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Review every three years.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/fair-access-protocols-in-school-admissions">Fair access protocols in school admissions</a></p>

<h3 id="capability-of-staff-and-teacher-appraisals">Capability of staff and teacher appraisals</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body or an individual governor.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-appraisal-and-capability-model-policy">Teacher appraisal and capability model policy</a></p>

<h3 id="central-record-of-recruitment-and-vetting-checks">Central record of recruitment and vetting checks</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Live document covering staff currently employed.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disqualification-under-the-childcare-act-2006">Disqualification under the childcare act 2006</a></p>

<h3 id="charging-and-remissions">Charging and remissions</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Governing body free to delegate approval  to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p>Applies directly to academies and free schools via their funding agreements.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/charging-for-school-activities">Charging for school activities</a></p>

<h3 id="data-protection">Data protection</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>further education colleges with 16 to 19 provision</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Under the the Data Protection (Charges and Information) Regulations 2018, schools must register with the <a rel="external" href="http://ico.org.uk/for_organisations/data_protection/registration">Information Commissioner’s Office</a>.</p>

<p>Review frequency: At least every two years, registration is annual.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/data-protection-and-privacy-privacy-notices">Data protection and privacy notices</a></p>

<h3 id="disqualification-under-the-childcare-act-2006">Disqualification under the childcare act 2006</h3>

<p>Applies to all schools, colleges and further education institutions where early years education is delivered.</p>

<p>Linked to safeguarding policies.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/disqualification-under-the-childcare-act-2006">Disqualification under the childcare act 2006</a></p>

<h3 id="freedom-of-information">Freedom of Information</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Applies to local authorities on behalf of  PRUs.</p>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Approval: Governing body free to determine how to implement.</p>

<p>Further information is on the <a rel="external" href="http://www.ico.org.uk/for_organisations/freedom_of_information">Information Commissioner’s Office website</a>.</p>

<h3 id="protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools-and-colleges">Protection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/protection-of-biometric-information-of-children-in-schools">Protection of biometric information of children in schools and colleges</a></p>

<h3 id="register-of-pupils-admission-to-school">Register of pupils’ admission to school</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Live document. 
Approval: The governing body free to delegate to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher or the proprietor must “cause to be kept” a register.</p>

<p>The register itself can be kept by appropriate school staff.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-attendance">School attendance</a></p>

<h3 id="register-of-pupils-attendance">Register of pupils’ attendance</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Live document.
Approval: The governing body of a school can delegate to the headteacher the keeping of the attendance register. The register can be kept  and updated daily by appropriate school staff.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-attendance">School attendance</a></p>

<h3 id="school-complaints">School complaints</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body or proprietor free to determine frequency of review.
Approval: Governing body free to delegate to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-complaints-procedures">School complaints procedures</a></p>

<h3 id="school-information-published-on-a-website">School information published on a website</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Live – must be updated as soon as possible after a change and at least annually. 
Approval: Governing body free to delegate to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/what-maintained-schools-must-publish-online">What maintained schools must publish online</a></p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/what-academies-free-schools-and-colleges-should-publish-online">What academies, free schools and colleges should publish online</a></p>

<h3 id="school-staff-driving-minibuses-driving-licences">School Staff Driving Minibuses: Driving Licences</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/driving-school-minibuses-advice-for-schools-and-local-authorities">School Staff Driving Minibuses: Driving Licences</a></p>

<h3 id="staff-discipline-conduct-and-grievance-procedures-for-addressing">Staff discipline, conduct and grievance (procedures for addressing)</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>For maintained schools the governing body free to determine frequency of review. All other establishments may want to include this policy but should refer to general employment law. 
For maintained schools the governing body must approve.</p>

<p>For academies the governing body is free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/staffing-and-employment-advice-for-schools">Staffing and employment advice for schools</a></p>

<h3 id="statement-of-procedures-for-dealing-with-allegations-of-abuse-against-staff">Statement of procedures for dealing with allegations of abuse against staff</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>further education colleges with 16 to 19 provision</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review and approval.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education">Keeping children safe in education</a></p>

<h3 id="teachers-pay">Teachers’ pay</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Review annually and governing body to approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-teachers-pay-and-conditions">Teachers’ pay and conditions</a></p>

<h2 id="pupil-well-being-and-behaviour">Pupil well being and behaviour</h2>

<h3 id="behaviour-principles-written-statement">Behaviour principles written statement</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Full governing body or a committee of the governing body to approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/governance-handbook">Governance handbook</a></p>

<h3 id="child-protection-policy-and-procedures">Child protection policy and procedures</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Review annually.
Governing body or proprietor to approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/keeping-children-safe-in-education">Keeping children safe in education</a></p>

<h3 id="early-years-foundation-stage-eyfs">Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS)</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Those delivering the EYFS are required to have policies and procedures on a range of issues covering safeguarding and welfare. These are set out in detail in the ‘Statutory framework for the Early Years Foundation Stage’.</p>

<p>Schools are not required to have separate policies to cover EYFS requirements where they are already met through an existing policy.  An EYFS profile assessment is required for each child during the academic year they reach the age of five (for most children this is the reception year in primary school) and nursery settings catering for children under three must complete a summary check when a child is aged two.</p>

<p>Review frequency varies, details are in the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/early-learning-and-childcare-guidance-for-early-years-providers">Statutory framework for the Early Years Foundation Stage</a>.</p>

<p>Governing body free to determine approval.</p>

<h3 id="first-aid-in-schools">First aid in schools</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/first-aid-in-schools">First aid in schools </a></p>

<h3 id="school-behaviour">School behaviour</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Headteacher free to determine frequency of review and approve.</p>

<p>[Behaviour and discipline in schools guidance for governing bodies]https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/behaviour-and-discipline-in-schools-guidance-for-governing-bodies)</p>

<h3 id="school-exclusion">School exclusion</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>pupil referral units (<abbr title="pupil referral unit">PRU</abbr>)</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-exclusion">School exclusion</a></p>

<h3 id="sex-education">Sex education</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Does not apply to maintained nursery schools.</p>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/sex-and-relationship-education">Sex and relationship education</a></p>

<h3 id="special-educational-needs">Special educational needs</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
</ul>

<p>The SEN Information Report should be updated annually and any changes to the information occurring during the year should be updated as soon as possible.
Full governing body or proprietor to approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/send-code-of-practice-0-to-25">The 0-25 Special Educational Needs and Disability Code of Practice.</a></p>

<h3 id="supporting-pupils-with-medical-conditions">Supporting pupils with medical conditions</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Review frequency: Governing bodies, proprietors and management committees free to determine.
Approval: Governing bodies of maintained schools, proprietors of academies, and management committees of pupil referral units.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/supporting-pupils-at-school-with-medical-conditions">Supporting pupils at school with medical conditions</a></p>

<h2 id="facilities">Facilities</h2>

<h3 id="health-and-safety">Health and safety</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Also applies to local authorities on behalf of community and voluntary-controlled schools and PRUs.</p>

<p>Governing body or proprietor or local authority free to determine frequency of review.
Employer free to determine how to implement and approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/health-and-safety-advice-for-schools">Health and safety advice for schools</a></p>

<h3 id="premises-management-documents">Premises management documents</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>independent schools, not state-funded</li>
  <li>sixth-form colleges</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
  <li>non-maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>There are many aspects of school premises that require safe management and maintenance such as asbestos, fire safety and statutory testing.</p>

<p>DfE provides additional non-statutory advice on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/asbestos-management-in-schools">asbestos management in schools</a>.</p>

<p>Independent schools, academies and free schools have sole responsibility.</p>

<p>For maintained schools, both local authorities and schools have responsibilities for the repair and maintenance of premises.</p>

<p>Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/standards-for-school-premises">Standards for school premises</a>
<a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/good-estate-management-for-schools/the-fundamentals-of-good-estate-management">Good estate management for schools</a></p>

<h2 id="governors-and-school-leaders">Governors and school leaders</h2>

<h3 id="equality-information-and-objectives-public-sector-equality-duty-statement-for-publication">Equality information and objectives (public sector equality duty) statement for publication</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Applies to local authorities on behalf of PRUs.</p>

<p>Review every four years and publish information annually.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p>Under specific duties, governing bodies, local authorities and proprietors are required to draw up and publish equality objectives every four years and annually publish information demonstrating how they are meeting the aims of the general public sector equality duty.</p>

<h3 id="governors-allowances-schemes-for-paying">Governors’ allowances (schemes for paying)</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Governing body free to delegate approval to a committee of the governing body, an individual governor or the headteacher.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/governance-handbook">Governance handbook</a></p>

<h3 id="instrument-of-government">Instrument of government</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review.
Full governing body to approve.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/governance-handbook">Governance handbook</a></p>

<h3 id="minutes-of-and-papers-considered-at-meetings-of-the-governing-body-and-its-committees">Minutes of, and papers considered at, meetings of the governing body and its committees</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
  <li>free schools, including university technical colleges and studio schools</li>
  <li>pupil referral units</li>
</ul>

<p>Full governing body or a committee of the governing body to approve as appropriate.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/constitution-of-governing-bodies-of-maintained-schools">Constitution of governing bodies of maintained schools</a></p>

<h3 id="register-of-business-interests-of-headteachers-and-governors">Register of business interests of headteachers and governors</h3>

<p>Applies to:</p>

<ul>
  <li>maintained schools, including maintained special schools</li>
  <li>academies</li>
</ul>

<p>Governing body free to determine frequency of review subject to the local authority scheme.
Governing body free to determine approval subject to the local authority scheme.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/governance-handbook">Governance handbook for maintain school</a>
<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/academies-financial-handbook">Academies financial handbook for academies</a></p>

</div>
